Collections.SubCollection.name: Collections.SubCollection
Collections.SubCollection.description:
SubCollection
A general-purpose Collection for dealing with nested Models

SubCollections can be assigned to properties of Models, i.e. Model._subCol (they will not be synced)
SubCollections contain SubModels and proxy all changes to original Model, while still
maintaining the built-in events
i.e. If we make Model.domains a SubCollection, you can still listen for changes on 'change:domains'

Nested model structure must be: { _id: 1, _body: { key: value } }

You should be able to nest SubCollections and SubModels, but this hasn't been tested

Mixins.Autosave.name: Mixins.Autosave
Mixins.Autosave.description:
Mixin for Views that allows them to trigger a model save event on user input
The collection is responsible for handling the save event
Also handles saving on 'enter' and 'tab' keyboard events

Autosave automatically binds events to elements on the model's "namespace" via the data attribute
The namespace is the model's "name" attribute lower-cased, e.g. Model.DomainSet > data-domainset
Example: <input type="text" data-domainset="name">

The namespace is the model's "name" attribute lower-cased, e.g. Model.DomainSet > data-domainset
Example: <input type="text" data-domainset="name">
